text.section:
The secretary of the Energy and Environment Cabinet shall take or cause to be taken such actions as may be necessary to:
Identify the geographical location of existing or potential markets for recovered materials and energy generated;
Identify the economic and technical barriers to the use of recovered materials and energy generated;
Identify sound technologies, techniques, and processes for resource recovery and energy generated applicable to both urban and rural areas of Kentucky;
Encourage the development of new uses for recovered materials; and
Encourage and promote the development of new markets for recovered materials.
